<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="13" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageId="6" pageNumber="13">
<taxonomicName LSID="89EECF1E-028A-D9E4-8992-37F91085F7E2" authority="Boiss., Diagn. Pl. Orient. ser. 1, 2: 32. 1843 [Mar 1843]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Trifolium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Trifolium setiferum" order="Fabales" pageId="6" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="setiferum">Trifolium setiferum Boiss., Diagn. Pl. Orient. ser. 1, 2: 32. 1843 [Mar 1843]</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="13" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph pageId="6" pageNumber="13">Type</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="6" pageNumber="13">
(holotype indicated by 
<bibRefCitation author="Zohary, M" journalOrPublisher="The Israel Academy of Sciences and Humanities, Jerusalem" pageId="15" pageNumber="22" refId="B62" refString="Zohary, M, Heller, D, 1984. The Genus Trifolium. The Israel Academy of Sciences and Humanities, Jerusalem" title="The Genus Trifolium." year="1984">Zohary and Heller 1984</bibRefCitation>
: 280): (Prov. Izmir) Montagne de Jenidje, May 1842, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="13">Boissier</emphasis>
(G).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="13" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="6" pageNumber="13">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="6" pageNumber="13">
Heads small; fruiting calyx inflated, calyx teeth with ciliolate base; longitudinal veins numerous; corolla longer than calyx. Seeds brown (
<bibRefCitation author="Zohary, M" journalOrPublisher="The Israel Academy of Sciences and Humanities, Jerusalem" pageId="15" pageNumber="22" refId="B62" refString="Zohary, M, Heller, D, 1984. The Genus Trifolium. The Israel Academy of Sciences and Humanities, Jerusalem" title="The Genus Trifolium." year="1984">Zohary and Heller 1984</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="13" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="6" pageNumber="13">Updated geographical distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="6" pageNumber="13">Calabria: - (new), Sicily: - (new).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="14" pageId="6" pageNumber="13" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="6" pageNumber="13">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="14" pageId="6" pageNumber="13">
Described from the Province of Izmir in Turkey, it is probably an eastern Mediterranean endemic naturally occurring only in Turkey and Greece, although many sources suggest it has a wider distribution based on its assumptive synonymy with 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Trifolium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Trifolium rumelicum" order="Fabales" pageId="6" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rumelicum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="13">Trifolium rumelicum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and/or 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Trifolium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Trifolium multistriatum" order="Fabales" pageId="6" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="multistriatum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="13">Trifolium multistriatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. We agree with 
<bibRefCitation author="Boissier, E" journalOrPublisher="H. Georg, Basilea" pageId="12" pageNumber="19" pagination="110 - 156" publicationUrl="10.5962/bhl.title.20323" refId="B2" refString="Boissier, E, 1872. Flora Orientalis. H. Georg, Basilea: 110 - 156" title="Flora Orientalis" url="10.5962/bhl.title.20323" year="1872">Boissier (1872)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Zohary, M" journalOrPublisher="The Israel Academy of Sciences and Humanities, Jerusalem" pageId="15" pageNumber="22" refId="B62" refString="Zohary, M, Heller, D, 1984. The Genus Trifolium. The Israel Academy of Sciences and Humanities, Jerusalem" title="The Genus Trifolium." year="1984">Zohary and Heller (1984)</bibRefCitation>
who separate this species from the latter based on the smaller size of the flower heads, the different shape of the leaves, the inflated calyces characterized by bristles at the base of the teeth. 
<bibRefCitation author="Pignatti, S" journalOrPublisher="Edagricole, Bologna" pageId="14" pageNumber="21" pagination="721 - 741" refId="B45" refString="Pignatti, S, 1982. Flora d'Italia. Edagricole, Bologna: 721 - 741" title="Flora d'Italia" year="1982">Pignatti (1982)</bibRefCitation>
does not report the species at all in Italy. All citations for Italy in fact have to be referred to 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Trifolium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Trifolium multistriatum" order="Fabales" pageId="6" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="multistriatum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="13">Trifolium multistriatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Zangheri, E" journalOrPublisher="CEDAM, Padova" pageId="15" pageNumber="22" pagination="328 - 329" refId="B59" refString="Zangheri, E, 1976. Flora Italica. CEDAM, Padova: 328 - 329" title="Flora Italica" year="1976">Zangheri 1976</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Greuter, W" journalOrPublisher="Conservatoire et Jardin Botaniques, Geneve" pageId="13" pageNumber="20" refId="B25" refString="Greuter, W, Burdet, HM, Long, G, 1989. Med-Checklist 4. Conservatoire et Jardin Botaniques, Geneve" title="Med-Checklist 4." year="1989">Greuter et al. 1989</bibRefCitation>
, Scoppola and Lattanzi, 2016). The species is only reported for Calabria by 
<bibRefCitation author="Zohary, M" journalOrPublisher="The Israel Academy of Sciences and Humanities, Jerusalem" pageId="15" pageNumber="22" refId="B62" refString="Zohary, M, Heller, D, 1984. The Genus Trifolium. The Israel Academy of Sciences and Humanities, Jerusalem" title="The Genus Trifolium." year="1984">Zohary and Heller (1984)</bibRefCitation>
, who probably refer to the same sample of 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Trifolium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Trifolium multistriatum" order="Fabales" pageId="6" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="multistriatum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="13">Trifolium multistriatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by Fiori of 1899 (FI, RO!) also cited under the name 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Trifolium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" infraspecific-rank="var." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Trifolium vesiculosum var. rumelicum" order="Fabales" pageId="7" pageNumber="14" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="vesiculosum" variety="rumelicum">
<pageBreakToken pageId="7" pageNumber="14" start="start">Trifolium</pageBreakToken>
vesiculosum var. rumelicum
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Greuter, W" journalOrPublisher="Conservatoire et Jardin Botaniques, Geneve" pageId="13" pageNumber="20" refId="B25" refString="Greuter, W, Burdet, HM, Long, G, 1989. Med-Checklist 4. Conservatoire et Jardin Botaniques, Geneve" title="Med-Checklist 4." year="1989">Greuter et al. (1989)</bibRefCitation>
report it as putative species for the mainland and Sicily also according to the synonymy with 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Trifolium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" infraspecific-rank="subsp." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Trifolium vesiculosum" order="Fabales" pageId="7" pageNumber="14" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subspecies" species="vesiculosum" subspecies="multistriatum">Trifolium vesiculosum subsp. multistriatum</taxonomicName>
(W.D.J.Koch) Arcang., indicated by 
<bibRefCitation author="Zangheri, E" journalOrPublisher="CEDAM, Padova" pageId="15" pageNumber="22" pagination="328 - 329" refId="B59" refString="Zangheri, E, 1976. Flora Italica. CEDAM, Padova: 328 - 329" title="Flora Italica" year="1976">Zangheri (1976)</bibRefCitation>
, who reported the entity in southern Italy and Sicily. Accordingly, no evidence was found to confirm its presence on the Italian territory.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
